How about the move to the top in the second quarter? Campbell at his best.

I always wanted to drive harness horses (couldnt with thoroughbreds) so I got my trainer/driver license after owning and breeding trotters/pacers for about five years. Broke two track records as a driver in the late 1980s. One at the Red Mile in Lexington and another at Yonkers.
Kassa Branca was a No Nukes colt, his dam was Friars Cutlin. I think we bought him as a yearling in the Lexington Kentucky sale.
I owned Kassa Branca with Bob Suslow (who was Chairman of Saks Fifth Avenue) and the great Brooklyn Dodgers pitcher, Ralph Branca. Ergo, the name Kassa Branca! (as in Casablanca)

The greatest win I ever had as an owner of standardbred horses. The 1988 Woodrow Wilson (purse $1.1 million) - a world record for two year olds!!!! Trained by Bill Popfinger and driven by the greatest driver of all time (Johnny Campbell). What a night! piped.video/watch?v=CH0Yfsqw…
